; OPTIMIZATION NOTES FOR XAUUSD (GOLD):
;=================================================================
;
; 1. WHY GOLD (XAUUSD):
;    - Safe-haven asset with clear consolidation/breakout patterns
;    - High liquidity during major sessions
;    - Strong momentum after consolidations
;    - Not directly correlated to forex or indices
;
; 2. EXPECTED PERFORMANCE:
;    - Win Rate: 45-55%
;    - Risk/Reward: 1:2 average (TP1 at 1:1, TP2 at 1:3)
;    - Trades/Month: 5-15
;    - Max Drawdown: 15-20%
;
; 3. MARKET DRIVERS:
;    - USD strength/weakness (inverse correlation)
;    - Inflation expectations (CPI data)
;    - Geopolitical events (safe-haven demand)
;    - Real yields (TIPS yields)
;    - Central bank policies (Fed, ECB)
;
; 4. HIGH-IMPACT NEWS EVENTS:
;    - NFP (Non-Farm Payrolls) - 1st Friday monthly
;    - CPI (Inflation) - Middle of month
;    - FOMC decisions - 8 times per year
;    - Geopolitical crises (unpredictable)
;
; 5. OPTIMAL TRADING TIMES (UTC):
;    - London-NY Overlap: 13:00-17:00 (BEST)
;    - US Session: 13:00-21:00
;    - Asian Session: 00:00-08:00 (lower volume)
;
; 6. BROKER CONSIDERATIONS:
;    - Spread: Should be < $0.30 ($30 per lot)
;    - Swap: Check overnight costs
;    - Margin: Gold requires higher margin
;    - Point value: Usually $1 per point per lot
;
; 7. CONSOLIDATION CHARACTERISTICS:
;    - Typical consolidation: 4-12 hours on H1
;    - ATR contracts before breakout
;    - Volume spikes on genuine breakouts
;    - False breakouts common at round numbers
;
; 8. KEY PRICE LEVELS:
;    - Round numbers: $1900, $1950, $2000, $2050
